  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Minimum of 5 visits with dementia diagnosis codes",
    "OR dementia drug fill (tacrine, donepezil, galantamine, rivastigmine, memantine)"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "The dementia phenotype algorithm identifies patients with presumptive Alzheimer's disease/dementia by selecting those who have either: (1) a minimum of 5 visits with any of the specified dementia ICD-9 diagnosis codes, OR (2) at least one fill of a dementia-specific medication. The algorithm uses a comprehensive list of ICD-9 codes covering various types of dementia including senile dementia, presenile dementia, vascular dementia, alcohol-related dementia, drug-induced dementia, Alzheimer's disease, Pick's disease, frontotemporal dementia, and dementia with Lewy bodies. The medication list includes cholinesterase inhibitors (tacrine, donepezil, galantamine, rivastigmine) and NMDA receptor antagonists (memantine). The final cohort is the union of patients meeting either the diagnosis criteria OR the medication criteria.",
